Interface SortProfiler

All Known Implementing Classes:
SortingAlgorithmCounter
public interface SortProfiler
The SortProfiler interface defines methods for profiling sorting algorithms by counting the number of executed statements.

Implementations of this interface should provide specific methods to count statements for various sorting algorithms, such as bubble sort, insertion sort, and selection sort, when applied to an array of MedicalRecords objects.
